# Local Port Isolation

When working in this repository, the runnable web app is **RodneyPortfolio** only. Keep a dedicated localhost port for it.

- Do not point multiple unrelated apps at the same local HTTP/HTTPS port.
- Treat port overlap as a blocking issue and fix `Properties/launchSettings.json` before further work.
- Prefer an explicit run command:
  - `dotnet run --project /workspaces/RodneyPortfolio/RodneyPortfolio.csproj --launch-profile http`
- Keep local routes local only; do not redirect localhost traffic to production domains.

## Required checks before testing

- Confirm `Properties/launchSettings.json` has the expected `applicationUrl` for the portfolio.
- Confirm the app identity on the port (e.g. portfolio home on `http://localhost:5076`).

